</figure>

<h3 id="the-arduino-sketch">The Arduino sketch</h3>

<p>The small sketch receives the data, turns on and off the motor and checks the distance from a wall. RoverBluetooth receives data from the Bluetooth modem and associates numbers to commands. For example, ‚Äú21‚Äù is interpreted as ‚Äúturn off the motor‚Äù. Here‚Äôs the list:</p>
<ul>
  <li>0-20 ‚Üí servo motor position</li>
  <li>21 ‚Üí motor off</li>
  <li>22 ‚Üí light on</li>
  <li>23 ‚Üí light off</li>
  <li>1000-1255 ‚Üí motor on, speed</li>
  <li>1500-1755 ‚Üí motor on, reverse gear, speed</li>
</ul>

